  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6771 sitting below the 6806 flip and under massive positive gamma walls at 6780-6800, dealers are positioned to buy this dip and sell any rally back toward 6800. The PIN regime with 90B+ in total GEX creates a strong mean-reversion environment, while the detected gex_surge indicates fresh options flow that should enhance the stabilizing forces. Key resistance at 6800 (61B gamma wall) will trigger heavy dealer selling, while support builds around 6780 where dealers must buy to hedge their long gamma positions.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 6780-6790 with limited upside past 6800.",
